<!--
  TRaid Autopilot — macOS launchd schedule.

  Fires ONLY at hours the US market could possibly be open, in Argentina local
  time (the Mac's clock), Mon-Fri: 11:00-17:00 ART. That window covers the US
  session (09:30-16:00 New York) in BOTH seasons — EDT (10:30-17:00 ART) and
  EST (11:30-18:00 ART) — so the machine never wakes at night or on weekends.

  The wrapper still runs a precise is_market_open() check for the exact
  open/close minute, US holidays, and the one edge hour that's open in only one
  season (a cheap Python skip — no brain, no tokens). So: no wasted wake-ups
  when we already know it's closed, and no false trades on a holiday inside the
  window. ~6 useful brain runs per trading day.

  Install:
    cp scripts/com.traid.autopilot.plist ~/Library/LaunchAgents/
    launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.traid.autopilot.plist
  Remove:
    launchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.traid.autopilot.plist

  NOTE: assumes the Mac's clock is set to Argentina time. If the timezone
  changes, adjust the Hour values (or switch to a US-anchored schedule).
-->
